headline: Starbucks Announces Store Closings, Layoffs. It Still Hasn’t Figured Out Its Turnaround.
summary: Starbucks is closing hundreds of coffee shops and laying off 900 employees as part of a $1 billion restructuring effort.  Starbucks had 18,734 locations as of June 29.  “We identified coffeehouses where we’re unable to create the physical environment our customers and partners expect, or where we don’t see a path to financial performance,” CEO Brian Niccol wrote in an open letter.

content.title: Starbucks Announces Store Closings, Layoffs. It Still Hasn’t Figured Out Its Turnaround.
content.summary: Starbucks is closing hundreds of coffee shops and laying off 900 employees as part of a $1 billion restructuring effort.  Starbucks had 18,734 locations as of June 29.  “We identified coffeehouses where we’re unable to create the physical environment our customers and partners expect, or where we don’t see a path to financial performance,” CEO Brian Niccol wrote in an open letter.
